Parktown Boys High School in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Parktown Boys' High School has released a statement saying it's noted concerns received via social media following the drowning of a Grade 8 pupil at an orientation camp in Brits in the North West. READ: Parktown Boys pupil's drowning probed Enoch Mpianzi's body was recovered on Friday morning after he went missing on Wednesday. In the statement, school authorities say they will not be engaging further about events leading up to the accident. The school says this because they don't want to hamper the investigation. Authorities say they'll release more information when they have it.